## Persuasion Layer Cues (Cialdini + NESB)

### Commitment Micro-Interactions

Design progressive commitment into conversion flows:

| Step | Level | UX Implementation |
|------|-------|-------------------|
| 1 | Micro | Scroll past hero, hover on CTA |
| 2 | Small | Click CTA (opens modal) |
| 3 | Medium | Enter email (2-step opt-in) |
| 4 | Medium | Answer preference question |
| 5 | Large | Complete form / Start trial |

### Trust Signal Placement

| Signal | Placement | Purpose |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| User Count | Hero, near CTA | Social proof at decision |
| Testimonials | After each section | Reinforce benefits |
| Logos | Below hero, footer | Authority transfer |
| Guarantees | Pricing, CTAs | Risk reversal |

**Rule:** Trust signals within 100px of every CTA.

### NESB Visual Cues

| Trigger | UX Implementation |
|---------|-------------------|
| **NEW** | "New" badges, "Just launched" labels |
| **EASY** | Step counters, time estimates |
| **SAFE** | Guarantee badges, security icons |
| **BIG** | Large outcome numbers, progress visuals |

### Five Drivers in UX

| Driver | UX Implementation |
|--------|-------------------|
| **Encourage Dreams** | Success celebrations, achievement animations |
| **Justify Failures** | Onboarding: "Not your fault" messaging |
| **Allay Fears** | Inline reassurances, FAQ tooltips |
| **Confirm Suspicions** | Comparison tables (old vs new) |
| **Throw Rocks** | "Unlike [old way]" messaging |
